.TH MARROW 1
.SH NAME
marrow \- portable distributed kernel (9P server)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B marrow
[
.I --port
.I port
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Marrow is a portable distributed kernel that provides 9P namespaces,
authentication, and service registry. It serves as the substrate layer
for graphics services like kryon.
.PP
Marrow implements:
.TP
9P2000 protocol server
Full 9P2000 file system protocol.
.TP
Authentication
dp9ik (Ed448), p9any, p9sk1, and secstore.
.TP
Service Registry
Dynamic service registration and discovery.
.TP
CPU Server
Plan 9-compatible CPU server (rcpu).
.TP
Namespace Management
Mount points and namespace operations.
.TP
System Devices
/dev/cons, /dev/fd, /proc, /env.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --port
TCP port to listen on (default: 17010).
.SH EXAMPLES
Start marrow on default port:
.EX
.B marrow
.EE
.PP
Start marrow on custom port:
.EX
.B marrow --port 17019
.EE
.SH SERVICES
Services can register with marrow to provide functionality:
.TP
kryon
Graphics/display service.
.TP
Custom services
Can be written to extend marrow.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR kryon (1),
.IR 9p (2),
.IR factotum (4)
.SH SOURCE
https://github.com/kryonlabs/marrow
